T1  - Foundations of Intrinsic Habit Formation
AU  - Rozen, Kareen
Y1  - 2010/07/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7302
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1341
EP  - 1373
VL  - 78
IS  - 4
KW  - Time-nonseparable preferences
KW  - linear habit formation
KW  - weaning
KW  - compensated separability
KW  - gains monotonicity
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7302
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We provide theoretical foundations for several common (nested) representations of intrinsic linear habit formation. Our axiomatization introduces an intertemporal theory of weaning a decision-maker from her habits using the device of compensation. We clarify differences across specifications of the model, provide measures of habit-forming tendencies, and suggest methods for axiomatizing time-nonseparable preferences.
ER  - 

